+# Project Rubric Completion — Intent Class Totalization Review v6
+
+Generated from `/mnt/data/canon-mini-agent-extracted/canon-mini-agent` after current artifact remeasurement, the prompt eval visibility patch, the eval semantic count self-verification patch, and the eval enforcement patch.
+
+The main state change is complete semantic hard-error burn-down for the current artifacts: `fn_with_any_error = 0` and `fn_error_rate = 0.0000`. The prompt eval header now reads live semantic manifest metrics, `compute_eval` derives semantic rates from counts, and eval enforcement now converts hard semantic/tlog/improvement regressions into explicit violations.
+
+## Variables
+
+| Symbol | Dimension | Score | Delta explanation |
+| --- | --- | ---: | --- |
+| `I` | Intelligence | 8.5 | Intent uncertainty, hard failure, report staleness, and eval violations are separated. |
+| `E` | Efficiency | 8.4 | False semantic error repair loops are reduced; prompt header reads live metrics and eval gate status. |
+| `C` | Correctness | 9.0 | Current graph has total function intent coverage; eval recomputes rates and fails hard regressions. |
+| `A` | Alignment | 8.7 | Extraction, semantic judgment, and eval display now have clearer authority boundaries. |
+| `R` | Robustness | 8.9 | Live semantic overlay, count-derived eval, and enforcement gates protect against stale report/rate fields. |
+| `P` | Performance | 7.4 | Error noise is lower; unknown-low-confidence remains high and should be reduced with heuristics. |
+| `S` | Scalability | 7.8 | Totalized function intent supports whole-graph traversal without null/error gaps. |
+| `D` | Determinism | 9.2 | `intent_missing = 0`; hard eval violations are thresholded and deterministic. |
+| `T` | Transparency | 9.2 | Prompt output exposes semantic contract, totalized intent, eval gate, violations, and warnings. |
+| `K` | Collaboration | 7.7 | Plan/rubric now distinguish artifact burn-down, self-verification, and enforcement validation. |
+| `X` | Empowerment | 8.0 | Next session can validate one narrow patch instead of rediscovering the semantic state. |
+| `B` | Benefit | 8.6 | Removes stale eval visibility and makes regressions visible as actionable gate failures. |
+| `L` | Learning | 8.5 | Low-confidence remains a measurable improvement target rather than a failure bucket. |
+| `F` | Future-proofing | 8.4 | Eval scoring is more resilient to projection lag, malformed rates, and unmeasured improvements. |
+
+## Equations
+
+```text
+G = (I·E·C·A·R·P·S·D·T·K·X·B·L·F)^(1/14)
+G_current = 8.51 / 10
+
+IntentSubsystem = mean(intent_coverage, low_confidence_signal, hard_error_truth, live_eval_visibility, deterministic_enforcement)
+IntentSubsystem_current = 9.25 / 10
+
+EvalGate = semantic_truth ∧ totalization ∧ tlog_health ∧ improvement_measured ∧ improvement_non_regressed
+
+good_target = max(I,E,C,A,R,P,S,D,T,K,X,B,L,F)
+```
+
+One-line explanation: the system is better because graph semantics are totalized, prompt eval visibility reads the live semantic sidecar, eval scoring derives semantic rates from counts, and enforcement gates now make regressions explicit.
+
+## Completed Work
+
+| Area | Status | Evidence |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| Wrapper total intent fallback | complete | `canon-rustc-v2/src/wrapper.rs` emits `unknown_low_confidence` for unclassified fn intent. |
+| Agent manifest demotion | complete | `src/semantic_manifest.rs` demotes generated optional placeholders out of hard error. |
+| Graph artifact remeasurement | complete | Current `graph.json` has `2392/2392` function intent coverage. |
+| Manifest sidecar burn-down | complete | Current `semantic_manifest_proposals.json` has `fn_with_any_error = 0`. |
+| Prompt eval visibility | patched | `src/prompt_inputs.rs` overlays live semantic manifest metrics over stale complexity report metrics. |
+| Eval semantic self-verification | patched | `src/evaluation.rs` derives semantic error, intent coverage, and low-confidence rates from counts. |
+| Eval enforcement | patched | `EvalEnforcement` records pass/fail, violations, warnings, and penalizes overall score on hard gate failures. |
+| Eval enforcement tests | added | Hard semantic/totalization failures fail; totalized low-confidence warns without failing. |
+| New eval enforcement build gate | pending | Rust toolchain unavailable in this environment; user should run build/test locally. |
+
+## Current Verdict
+
+```text
+max(intent_coverage, manifest_truth, live_eval_visibility, eval_enforcement, determinism) = good
+```
+
+Validated current state:
+
+```text
+G.intent_classified / G.fn_total = 2392 / 2392
+G.intent_missing = 0
+M.fn_with_any_error = 0
+M.fn_error_rate = 0.0000
+Prompt eval semantic overlay = patched
+Eval semantic count self-verification = patched
+Eval enforcement gates = patched
+```
+
+Remaining work:
+
+```text
+cargo build && cargo test
+rerun complexity report/eval
+confirm latest.json/tlog semantic metrics use count-derived eval rates and eval_enforcement_* fields
+then reduce unknown_low_confidence without treating optional uncertainty as failure
+```
